      "grammar": {
        "title": "A1 Grammar Focus: Present Tense & Basic Questions",
        "sections": [
          {
            "heading": "1. Personal Pronouns",
            "content": "German pronouns change based on who you're talking to:\n- **Ich** = I\n- **du** = you (informal, e.g., friends)\n- **Sie** = you (formal, e.g., teachers, strangers)\n- **er/sie/es** = he/she/it\n- **wir** = we\n- **ihr** = you (plural informal, e.g., friends)\n- **sie** = they"
          },
          {
            "heading": "2. Verb 'sein' (to be)",
            "content": "Used for identity, origin, and condition:\n- Ich **bin** Lena. (I am Lena.)\n- Du **bist** Tom. (You are Tom.)\n- Er **ist** Student. (He is a student.)\n- Wir **sind** hier. (We are here.)\n- Sie **sind** nett. (They are nice.)"
          },
          {
            "heading": "3. Verb 'heißen' (to be called)",
            "content": "Only used for names:\n- Ich **heiße** Anna. (My name is Anna.)\n- Wie **heißt** du? (What is your name?)\n→ Note: 'heißen' is irregular — no -e ending in 1st person!"
          },
          {
            "heading": "4. Question Words",
            "content": "Start questions with these words:\n- **Wer?** = Who?\n- **Was?** = What?\n- **Wo?** = Where?\n- **Wann?** = When?\n- **Warum?** = Why?\n- **Wie?** = How?"
          },
          {
            "heading": "5. Prepositions: aus / in",
            "content": "- **aus** + Dativ = from (a country/city): Ich komme **aus Berlin**.\n- **in** + Dativ = in (a city): Ich wohne **in München**.\n→ Use Dativ case after these prepositions!"
          },
          {
            "heading": "6. Adjectives after 'sein'",
            "content": "Adjectives stay in basic form after 'sein':\n- Ich bin **jung**. (I am young.)\n- Das ist **schön**. (That is nice.)\n- Berlin ist **groß**. (Berlin is big.)"
          },
          {
            "heading": "7. Negation with 'nicht'",
            "content": "Place 'nicht' at the end of the sentence or before the word you negate:\n- Ich bin **nicht** aus Paris.\n- Er ist **nicht** Student.\n- Ich heiße **nicht** Tom."
          }
        ]
      },
